(11510, 1, '2016-11-09 11:55:33', '2016-11-09 11:55:33', '<h2>Exhilarating Things to do in Bangalore</h2>\r\nBangalore is the city of green gardens, pleasant weather, theatre, coffee houses and most importantly the IT hub. There are many exhilarating <a href="https://indiator.com"><strong>things to do in Bangalore</strong></a> which are truly attracted the travelers and give them a remarkable experience.\r\n\r\nThe list of some of <strong>the most fascinating things to do in Bangalore</strong> are mentioned below:\r\n\r\n<strong>Have delectable Dosa in Vidyarthi Bhavan</strong> – An old-aged restaurant which start in the year 1943 especially for serving the students, is now become the brand name of the town. The restaurant offers the relish taste of the food at shockingly low prices, which you haven’t found any other place of the city. This is the most popular place to visit in Bangalore, the fame of the place brings the people from all over the globe.\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-157" src="https://indiator.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Dosa_and_ghee.jpg" alt="dosa_and_ghee" width="800" height="533" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Admire the nature in Lalbagh</strong> – Spreading over the huge area of 240 acres of land, house a vast assortment of interesting things like a glass house, a lake, an aquarium, an oldest rock of the world, an enormous collection of flora and fauna and many other things which are the major<a href="https://indiator.com"> <strong>tourist attractions of Bangalore</strong>.</a><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-158" src="https://indiator.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Glasshouse_and_fountain_at_lalbagh.jpg" alt="glasshouse_and_fountain_at_lalbagh" width="1800" height="1130" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Have a sip of Coffee</strong> – You drink coffee many times in many restaurants, some of them are really big and branded. But, the coffee on the RIP India coffee house has been proved to be the best in all.\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-159" src="https://indiator.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/coffee.jpg" alt="coffee" width="761" height="426" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Memorize the blockbuster Sholay</strong> – See the Ramgadh where the Sholay movie has been shot. The rock where the all Gabbar Singh shots are picturised and the Hema Malini climax song. The place is now-a-days used by visitors for camping, trekking and delve into the nature.\r\n\r\n<strong style="font-size: 1.0625rem;"><img class="alignnone wp-image-160" src="https://indiator.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Ramanagaram-Trek-of-Sholay-fame.jpg" alt="ramanagaram-trek-of-sholay-fame" width="761" height="424" />Attraction for art lovers</strong><span style="font-size: 1.0625rem;"> – Venkatappa Art Gallery is one of the amazing and interesting <strong>sightseeing place in Bangalore</strong>. This two storey building has art gallery as well as an archaeological museum showcased with stunning paintings of M F Hussain, Hariram, Hanumiah and other influential artists. Also displayed bullets, swords, daggers and other armory from the medieval era.</span>\r\n\r\n<strong style="font-size: 1.0625rem;"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-161" src="https://indiator.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Venkatappa-Art-Gallery.jpeg" alt="venkatappa-art-gallery" width="800" height="448" />Shop at Flea Market</strong><span style="font-size: 1.0625rem;"> – Bangalore is the best place to shop everything from clothes to handmade artifacts available at reasonable rates. Some of the flea markets of the town also offered live music and performances to chill out the people.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-162" src="https://indiator.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/BeFunky_anjuna_flea_market1.jpg.jpg" alt="befunky_anjuna_flea_market1-jpg" width="775" height="581" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Go for Karting and Rock Climbing</strong> – Rock climbing and Karting are the two most exciting sport for adventurous and fun lovers who come to the town for some excitement. You can do Karting at Kanakpura Main road and climbing at Residency road.\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-163" src="https://indiator.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/rock-climbing.jpg" alt="rock-climbing" width="763" height="453" />\r\n\r\n<strong>See the powerful stage show</strong> – Spending time in the movie hall, go to watch the live<strong> stage show at Ranga Shankara</strong>. It’s an iconic stage, which gives chance to not only the well-known performers, but also to the newcomers too.\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-164" src="https://indiator.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/ranga-shankara.jpg" alt="ranga-shankara" width="785" height="483" />\r\n\r\nAmong all these splendid things to do, Bangalore has some more activities and places to visit. So, it’s better to plan and book a <a href="https://indiator.com"><strong>Bangalore tour package</strong> </a>rather than to read it on the internet and take a virtual glimpses of the natural and ancient sights of Bangalore.', 'Top Things to do in Bangalore, India', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'top-things-to-do-in-bangalore-india', '', '', '2016-11-09 11:55:33', '2016-11-09 11:55:33', '', 0, 'http://localhost/Destinations/?p=11510', 0, 'post', '', 0),
